SNP filtering

dDocent uses FreeBayes to call SNPs and write a VCF-file TotalrawSNPs.vcf. This data set was filtered to remove low quality and artefactual SNP sites, paralogs and low quality individuals based on levels of missing data, minimum/maximum read depth, genotype call rate, and minor allele frequencies. Contigs may contain more than one SNP; the script rad_haplotyper.pl was used to create haplotypes for each locus.

Raw data

Individuals/Populations sampled

Generate a list of all individuals included in the SNP data set called by FreeBayes in the dDocent pipeline.


vcfsamplenames data/VCF/temp/TotalRawSNPs.vcf > data/VCF/Ind_raw

Use Ind_raw file to write text files of individuals in each library and in regional groupings.


# import individuals in raw data set ----
Ind_RAW <- read.table("data/VCF/Ind_raw", 
                      header = FALSE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE,
                      col.names = "SAMPLE_ID") %>%
  separate(SAMPLE_ID, into = c("POP", "temp"), sep = "_", remove = FALSE) %>%
  select(-temp)

count(Ind_RAW, POP)

# create files with individuals by population ----
temp <- Ind_RAW %>%
  filter(POP == "AFL") %>%
  select(SAMPLE_ID)

write.table(temp, "data/VCF/Ind_AFL",
            col.names = FALSE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

temp <- Ind_RAW %>%
  filter(POP == "BSL") %>%
  select(SAMPLE_ID)

write.table(temp, "data/VCF/Ind_BSL",
            col.names = FALSE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

temp <- Ind_RAW %>%
  filter(POP == "JKF") %>%
  select(SAMPLE_ID)

write.table(temp, "data/VCF/Ind_JKF",
            col.names = FALSE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

temp <- Ind_RAW %>%
  filter(POP == "SLT") %>%
  select(SAMPLE_ID)

write.table(temp, "data/VCF/Ind_SLT",
            col.names = FALSE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

temp <- Ind_RAW %>%
  filter(POP == "ULM") %>%
  select(SAMPLE_ID)

write.table(temp, "data/VCF/Ind_ULM",
            col.names = FALSE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

Compare Individual & SNP stats

Use VCFtools to create stats files for depth, missing data, heterozygosity and site quality for the raw data.


vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/TotalRawSNPs.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN_raw --depth
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/TotalRawSNPs.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN_raw --site-mean-depth
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/TotalRawSNPs.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN_raw --site-quality
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/TotalRawSNPs.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN_raw --missing-indv
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/TotalRawSNPs.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN_raw --missing-site
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/TotalRawSNPs.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN_raw --het
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/TotalRawSNPs.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN_raw--geno-depth

Genotype depth distribution

Import genotype depth per locus and individual and format into tidy data set.


gdepth <- read.table("data/VCF/MUN_raw.gdepth",
                         header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  unite(col = LOCUS, CHROM, POS, sep = "_", remove = TRUE) %>%
  gather(key = IND, value = GDEPTH, 2:171) %>%
  mutate(MISSING = ifelse(GDEPTH == -1, "missing", "genotyped")) %>%
  mutate(GDEPTH = as.numeric(gsub(-1, 0, GDEPTH))) %>%
  mutate(GDEPTHBIN = cut(GDEPTH, 
                         breaks = c(0, 2, 5, 10, 25, 50, 100, 500, max(GDEPTH)),
                         labels = c("<3", "<5", "<10", "<25", "<50", "<100", "<500", ">500")))

Data set consists of 8598576 data points (individuals/locus combinations).

Create heatmap of genotype depth:

# library(viridis)
ggplot(gdepth, aes(x = IND, y = LOCUS)) + 
  geom_tile(aes(fill = GDEPTHBIN)) + 
  scale_fill_viridis(direction = -1, option = "viridis",
                     name = 'genotype depth',
                     discrete = TRUE) +
  labs(x = "individual", y = "locus") +
  theme(axis.text.x=element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.x=element_blank(),
        axis.text.y=element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.y=element_blank(),
        legend.position="bottom")

Choose threshold values for quality score, coverage, missing data, minor alleles and mapping/variant calling artifacts

Filter 0: Remove LQ individuals

# remove LQ individuals
LQind <- ind_stats_raw %>%
  filter(MISS_MUN_raw > 0.95) %>%
  select(INDV)
View(LQind)
# write file
write.table(LQind, "data/VCF/LQ_raw.ind",
            col.names = FALSE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

Remove low quality individuals.

Visualize stats:

# load stats files ----
ind_stats_F0 <- read.ind.stats(dir = "data/VCF", vcf = "MUN.F0") %>%
  separate(INDV, into = c("SP", "LIB", "SAMPLE_ID"), sep = "_", remove = FALSE)
loc_stats_F0 <- read.loc.stats(dir = "data/VCF/", vcf = "MUN.F0")

Filter 1: Confidence in SNP call

The QUAL column of a VCF file is a phred based score indicating the probability that the variant shown in the ALT column is wrong. Given the Phred quality score (Q), and the probability that a base is incorrectly called (P), Q = -10(Log10P).

A quality score of 20 indicates, a 1 in 100 chance that the SNP site has been called incorrectly (i.e.99% probability that correct call).

Filter loci with quality score < 20 and/or a minor allele count < 2, then code genotypes with less than 3 reads are coded as missing


# filter LQ SNP calls
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F0.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/temp/MUN.F1 --remove data/VCF/LQ_raw.ind --minQ 20 --minDP 3 --recode --recode-INFO-all

# query stats
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F1.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F1 --depth
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F1.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F1 --site-mean-depth
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F1.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F1 --missing-indv
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F1.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F1 --missing-site
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F1.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F1 --het
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F1.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F1 --geno-depth

Analyze stats post-filtering.

# load stats files ----
ind_stats_F1 <- read.ind.stats(dir = "data/VCF", vcf = "MUN.F1")
loc_stats_F1 <- read.loc.stats(dir = "data/VCF/", vcf = "MUN.F1")

Data set contains 169 individuals and 495835 SNP sites.

Removing loci with minor allele counts < 3 results in a reduction in the number of the (maximum) SNPs per locus, removing low quality SNP calls will have the same effect.

p1 <- loc_stats_raw %>%
  count(CHR) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = n)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, color = "black", fill = "darkorange") + 
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 85)) +
  labs(x = "") +
  theme_standard
p2 <- loc_stats_F1 %>%
  count(CHR) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = n)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, color = "black", fill = "darkorange") + 
  labs(x = "number of SNPs per locus") +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 85)) +
  theme_standard
m1a <- multiplot(p1, p2, cols=1)

Coding genotypes with low read depth (< 3) as missing, results in an overall increase in missing data per locus and a shift in more individuals with missing data > 90% - this is because individuals (and loci) with coverage issues are now characterized by higher missing data.

iraw <- read.table("data/VCF/MUN_raw.imiss",
                    header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  select(INDV, F_MISS) %>%
  rename(raw = F_MISS)
imiss <- read.table("data/VCF/MUN.F1.imiss",
                    header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  select(INDV, F_MISS) %>%
  rename(F1 = F_MISS)
imiss <- left_join(imiss, iraw)
p1 <- ggplot(imiss, aes(x = raw, y = F1)) +
  geom_point(shape = 1) +
  geom_abline(slope = 1, color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 0.85)) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 0.85)) +
  labs(x = "indv missing data raw", y = "indv missing data F1") +
  theme_standard
lraw <- read.table("data/VCF/MUN_raw.lmiss",
                    header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  select(CHR, POS, F_MISS) %>%
  rename(raw = F_MISS)
lmiss <- read.table("data/VCF/MUN.F1.lmiss",
                    header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  select(CHR, POS, F_MISS) %>%
  rename(F1 = F_MISS)
lmiss <- left_join(lmiss, lraw)
p2 <- ggplot(lmiss, aes(x = raw, y = F1)) +
  geom_point(shape = 1) +
  geom_abline(slope = 1, color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  labs(x = "loci missing data raw", y = "loci missing data F1") +
  theme_standard
m1b <- multiplot(p1, p2, cols=2)

Filter 2: Genotype call rate and allowed missing data per indv

Remove loci with genotype call rate < 10% and mean read depth per locus across all individuals < 5.


vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F1.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/temp/MUN.F2a --max-missing 0.1 --min-meanDP 5 --recode --recode-INFO-all

vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F2a.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F2a --missing-indv

Flag individuals with > 90% missing data

# determine cutoff
imiss <- read.table("data/VCF/MUN.F2a.imiss", 
           header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE, sep = "\t") 
ggplot(imiss, aes(x = F_MISS)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.05, color = "black", fill = "darkorange") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0.95, color = "darkred", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  theme_standard

imiss <- imiss %>%
  filter(F_MISS > 0.95) %>%
  select(INDV)
View(imiss)
write.table(imiss, "data/VCF/F2a_LQ.indv",
            col.names = TRUE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

Remove flagged individuals, then remove loci with genotype call rate < 30%.


vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F2a.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/temp/MUN.F2b --remove data/VCF/F2a_LQ.indv --recode --recode-INFO-all

vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F2b.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/temp/MUN.F2c --max-missing .3 --recode --recode-INFO-all

vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F2c.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F2c --missing-indv

Identify individuals with > 80% missing data

# determine cutoff
imiss <- read.table("data/VCF/MUN.F2c.imiss", 
           header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE, sep = "\t") 
ggplot(imiss, aes(x = F_MISS)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.05, color = "black", fill = "darkorange") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0.9, color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  theme_standard

imiss <- imiss %>%
  filter(F_MISS > 0.9) %>%
  select(INDV)
write.table(imiss, "data/VCF/F2c_LQ.indv",
            col.names = TRUE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

Remove flagged individuals and generate missing data stats per locus for all libraries.


# remove flagged individuals
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F2c.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/temp/MUN.F2d --remove data/VCF/F2c_LQ.indv --recode --recode-INFO-all

Compare distribution of missing data per locus per library. Mean proportion of missing data indicated.

# create empty list
loc_missing <- list()
# import missing data per locus
loc_missing[[1]] <- read.table("data/VCF/ULM.lmiss", 
                        header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  select(CHR, POS, F_MISS) %>%
  mutate(POP = "ULM")
# import missing data per locus
loc_missing[[2]] <- read.table("data/VCF/SLT.lmiss", 
                        header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  select(CHR, POS, F_MISS) %>%
  mutate(POP = "SLT")
loc_missing[[3]] <- read.table("data/VCF/JKF.lmiss", 
                        header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  select(CHR, POS, F_MISS) %>%
  mutate(POP = "JKF")
loc_missing[[4]] <- read.table("data/VCF/BSL.lmiss", 
                        header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  select(CHR, POS, F_MISS) %>%
  mutate(POP = "BSL")
loc_missing[[5]] <- read.table("data/VCF/AFL.lmiss", 
                        header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  select(CHR, POS, F_MISS) %>%
  mutate(POP = "AFL")
# create data frame with all information
loc_missing <- ldply(loc_missing, data.frame)
ggplot(loc_missing, aes(x = F_MISS)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = .1, color = "black", fill = "darkorange") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = 0.5),
             color = "darkred", linetype = "dashed", size = 0.5) +
  labs(x = "missing data per locus") +
  facet_grid(POP ~ .) +
  theme_standard

Flag loci that were not called in > 50% of individuals in a given population.

# identify loci with high missing data in each library
SNPs <- filter(loc_missing, F_MISS > 0.5) %>%
  arrange(CHR, POS)
count(SNPs, POP)
LQloci <- SNPs %>%
  select(CHR, POS) %>%
  unique()
View(LQloci)
# Write contig/position to file
write.table(LQloci, file = "data/VCF/LQ_F2d.loci", 
            col.names= FALSE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

# plot missing data per indv ----
p1 <- ggplot(ind_stats_F2, aes(x = MISS_MUN.F2)) +

                 color = "red", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +

  mutate(PROB = 10^(-QUAL/10))

  rename(depth = loc_stats_F2.MEAN_DEPTH_MUN.F2, qual = site_qual.QUAL)

  geom_point(size = 1) +

                 color = "red", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +

                 color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  geom_hline(aes(yintercept = mean(qual, na.rm = TRUE)),
                 color = "red", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  geom_hline(aes(yintercept = 20),
                 color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  labs(x = "mean depth per locus", y = "SNP quality") +
  theme_standard

Filter 3: Remove loci with inconsistent coverage

Compare distribution of depth coverage per locus per library. Identify loci that have low coverage and/or high variance in a given library (compared to other libraries).

Identify loci with large variance in mean depth across libraries and/or individuals:

# mean depth across all individuals
depth_comp <- read.table("data/VCF/MUN.F2.ldepth.mean", 
                   header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  distinct(CHROM, .keep_all = TRUE) %>%
  select(-POS) %>%
  mutate(STD_DEPTH = sqrt(VAR_DEPTH),
         COEFF_VAR = STD_DEPTH/MEAN_DEPTH*100)

Compare mean across all individual to mean weighted by library and standard deviation of mean across all individual to mean of mean depth per library (linear regression (w/95% CI)):

p1 <- ggplot(depth_comp, aes(x = MEAN_DEPTH, y = VAR_DEPTH)) +
  geom_point(shape = 1) +
  geom_smooth(method = lm, se = TRUE,
              color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", fill = "lightblue") +
  labs(x = "mean across all indv", y = "variation") +
  theme_standard
p2 <- ggplot(depth_comp, aes(x = MEAN_DEPTH, y = COEFF_VAR)) +
  geom_point(shape = 1) +
  geom_smooth(method = lm, se = TRUE,
              color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", fill = "lightblue") +
  labs(x = "mean depth", y = "coefficient of variance") +
  theme_standard
p3 <- ggplot(depth_comp, aes(x = COEFF_VAR)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 10, color = "black", fill = "darkorange") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 175, color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", size = 0.5) +
  labs(x = "coeff var depth") +
  theme_standard
m3 <- multiplot(p1, p3, p2, cols=2)

Flag loci that have high variation in mean coverage between individuals and between libraries.

# identify loci high variation in coverage
contigs_var <- depth_comp %>%
  filter(COEFF_VAR > 175)
SNPs_var <- filter(depth_comp, CHROM %in% contigs_var$CHROM) %>%
  distinct(CHROM, POS)
# identify loci with low mean depth across all individuals
SNP_mean <- depth_comp %>%
  filter(MEAN_DEPTH < 10) %>%
  distinct(CHROM, POS)
SNPs <- bind_rows(SNPs_var, SNP_mean) %>%
  distinct(CHROM, POS)
# Write contig/position to text file, use file with vcftools to remove positions from dataset 
write.table(SNPs, file = "data/VCF/LQ_F3.loci", 
            col.names= FALSE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

Filter 4: Minimum mean depth and genotype call rate

Remove loci with minimum mean depth across all individuals > 15 and genotype call rate of < 75%.


vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F3.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/temp/MUN.F4 --min-meanDP 15 --max-missing 0.75 --recode --recode-INFO-all

m5 <- multiplot(p1, p2, p3, p4, cols=2)

Data set contains 199200 SNP sites.

Filter 5: Allele balance

AB: Allele balance at heterozygous sites: a number between 0 and 1 representing the ratio of reads showing the reference allele to all reads, considering only reads from individuals called as heterozygous

Allele balance is the ratio of reads for reference allele to all reads, considering only reads from individuals called as heterozygous. Values range from 0 - 1; allele balance (for real loci) should be approx. 0.5. Filter contigs SNPs for which the with allele balance < 0.25 and > 0.75.

read.table("data/VCF/temp/MUN.F4.AB",
           col.names = "AB", stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = AB)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.025, color = "black", fill = "darkorange") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0.5, color = "red", linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0.25, color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0.75, color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed") +
  labs(x = "Allele balance") +
  theme_standard

Filter contigs with SNP calls with AB > 0.25, AB > 0.75; retain loci very close to 0 (retain loci that are fixed variants). Remove genotypes if the quality sum of the reference or alternate allele was 0.

Remaining SNPs: 174,356.

Filter 6: quality/depth ratio


# site depth

# quality score
mawk '!/#/'  MUN.F5.vcf | cut -f1,2,6 > MUN.F5.loci.qual

# depth

Filter 7: mapping quality

Remove loci based on ratio of mapping quality for reference and alternate allele, i.e.sites that have a high discrepancy between the mapping qualities of two alleles.

temp <- read.table("data/VCF/temp/MUN.F6.MQM", col.names = "MQM")
mapqual <- read.table("data/VCF/temp/MUN.F6.MQMR", col.names = "MQMR")
mapqual <- bind_cols(mapqual, temp) %>%
  mutate(ratio = MQM/MQMR)
filter <- mapqual %>%
  filter(ratio < 0.25 | ratio > 1.75)
ggplot(mapqual, aes(x = MQM, y = MQMR)) +
  geom_point(shape = 1) + 
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, size = 1, color = "red", linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 4, size = 1, color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 0.571, size = 1, color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_point(data = filter, aes(x = MQM, y = MQMR), color = "red", shape = 1) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 64)) +
  theme_standard

Filter 8: Strand balance

SRF: Number of reference observations on the forward strand SAF: Number of alternate observations on the forward strand SRR: Number of reference observations on the reverse strand SAR: Number of alternate observations on the reverse strand

Paired end reads should not overlap, and a SNP site should only be covered by either the forward or reverse read (strand).


SAF <- read.table("data/VCF/temp/MUN.F7.SAF",
                  col.names = "SAF")

SAR <- read.table("data/VCF/temp/MUN.F7.SAR",
                  col.names = "SAR")

strands <- bind_cols(SAF, SAR)

SRF <- read.table("data/VCF/temp/MUN.F7.SRF",
                  col.names = "SRF")

strands <- bind_cols(strands, SRF)

SRR <- read.table("data/VCF/temp/MUN.F7.SRR",
                  col.names = "SRR")

strands <- bind_cols(strands, SRR) %>%
  mutate(ratioA = SAF/SAR, ratioR = SRF/SRR)

ggplot(strands, aes(x = SAF, y = SAR)) +
  geom_point(shape = 1) +
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 0.1, color = "blue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 100, color = "blue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  theme_standard

Remove SNP sites that have > 100x more forward alternate reads than reverse alternate reads and > 100x more forward reverse reads than reverse alternate reads.


vcffilter -f "SAF / SAR > 100 & SRF / SRR > 100 | SAR / SAF > 100 & SRR / SRF > 100" -s MUN.F7.vcf > MUN.F8.vcf

mawk '!/#/' MUN.F8.vcf | wc -l

Number of SNPs remaining: 47,103.

Filter 9: Properly paired status

PAIRED: Proportion of observed alternate alleles which are supported by properly paired read fragments PAIREDR: Proportion of observed reference alleles which are supported by properly paired read fragments

Identify loci with only unpaired reads mapping to them - an artifact introduced due de novo reference assembly. Compare number of paired reads mapping the reference and the alternate alleles to identify discrepancy in the paired status for reads supporting reference and alternate alleles.

Number of SNPs in data set: 45,667.

Filter 10: Maximum depth & Quality

Identify distribution of depth (based on original data set) to identify loci with excess coverage.

Original number of individuals in data set is 170 (INFO flags in filtered data set are are based on original number of individuals in data set).

Create file with the original site depth and quality score for each site:

Calculate average depth and standard deviation:

# depth
depth <- read.table("data/VCF/temp/MUN.F10.DEPTH",
                    col.names = "depth")
# quality score
qual <- read.table("data/VCF/temp/MUN.F10.loci.qual",
                   col.names = c("locus", "pos", "qual"))
# mean depth
mean_depth <- mean(depth$depth)
# standard deviation
std <- sd(depth$depth)
# calculate cutoff
cutoff <- sum(mean_depth + (2*std))
# identify SNPs with excess (i.e. depth > mean depth + 1 standard deviation
# and quality score < 2x the depth at that site
df <- bind_cols(qual, depth) %>%
  mutate(qualcutoff = 2*depth)
removeloc <- df %>%
  filter(depth > cutoff) %>%
  filter(qual < 2*depth)
# plot
ggplot(df, aes(x = depth, y = qual)) +
  geom_point(shape = 1) +
  geom_point(data = removeloc, aes(x = depth, y = qual), color = "red", shape = 1) +
  geom_line(data = df, aes(x = depth, y = qualcutoff), color = "blue",  linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = cutoff, color = "blue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  theme_standard

LQ <- removeloc %>%
  select(locus, pos)
write.table(LQ, "data/VCF/temp/LQ_F10.loci", 
            col.names = FALSE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

Mean depth per locus (across all indivuals) is 4674.6899512 and the standard deviation is 3465.4239393.

Filter SNP site with depth > mean depth + 1 standard deviation = 1.160553810^{4} and that have quality scores < 2x the depth at that site and output depth per site.

# even though genotype w/ <3 reads are coded as missing the read depth is still included
gdepth <- read.table("data/VCF/MUN.F12.gdepth",
                         header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) %>%
  unite(col = LOCUS, CHROM, POS, sep = "_", remove = TRUE) %>%
  gather(key = IND, value = GDEPTH, 2:169) %>%
  mutate(MISSING = ifelse(GDEPTH %in% c(-1, 1, 2), "missing", "genotyped")) %>%
  mutate(GDEPTH = as.numeric(gsub(-1, 1, GDEPTH))) %>% # replace as 1 because 0 will become NA for bin
  mutate(GDEPTHBIN = cut(GDEPTH, 
                         breaks = c(0, 1, 10, 25, 50, 100, 500, max(GDEPTH)),
                         labels = c("missing", "<10", "<25", "<50", "<100", "<500", ">500")))
count(gdepth, GDEPTHBIN)

Filter 13: Excess heterozygosity

Identify SNPs with more than 0.5 heterozygosity and significant.

# calculate observed heterozygosity
hwe <- read.table("data/VCF/MUN.F12.hwe", 
                  stringsAsFactors = FALSE, header = TRUE) %>%
  select(-ChiSq_HWE) %>%
  separate(`OBS.HOM1.HET.HOM2.`, 
           into = c("obs_hom1", "obs_het", "obs_hom2"), 
           sep = "/", convert = TRUE) %>%
  separate(`E.HOM1.HET.HOM2.`, 
           into = c("exp_hom1", "exp_het", "exp_hom2"), 
           sep = "/", convert = TRUE) %>%   
  mutate(Ho = obs_het/(obs_hom1 + obs_hom2 + obs_het),
         He = exp_het/(exp_hom1 + exp_hom2 + exp_het)) %>%
  select(CHR, POS, obs_hom1, exp_hom1, obs_hom2, exp_hom2, P_HET_DEFICIT, obs_het, exp_het, P_HET_EXCESS, Ho, He, P_HWE)

Distribution of observed heterozygosity.

ggplot(hwe, aes(x = Ho)) + 
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.05, color = "black", fill = "darkorange") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0.5, color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  labs(x = "observed heterozygosity") +
  theme_standard

Identify loci with heterozygosity > 0.5, then correct p-values for multiple comparisons using Benjamini-Hochberg method.

# identify contigs with SNPs with Ho > 0.5 & significant
excess_hwe <- hwe %>%
  filter(Ho > 0.5) %>%
  mutate(p_adj = p.adjust(P_HET_EXCESS), method = "fdr") %>%
  filter(p_adj < 0.05)
contigs <- hwe %>%
  filter(CHR %in% excess_hwe$CHR) %>%
  select(CHR) %>%
  unique()
# identify all SNPs on contigs
SNPs <- hwe %>%
  filter(CHR %in% contigs$CHR) %>%
  select(CHR, POS)
View(SNPs)
# Write contig/position to text file, use file with vcftools to remove positions from dataset 
write.table(SNPs, file = "data/VCF/hetexcess.loci", 
            col.names= FALSE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

Remove SNPs with excess heterozygosity and contigs with more than one SNP w/excess heterozygosity.


vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F12.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/temp/MUN.F13 --exclude-positions data/VCF/hetexcess.loci --recode --recode-INFO-all

vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F13.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F13 --depth
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F13.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F13 --site-mean-depth
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F13.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F13 --missing-indv
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F13.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F13 --missing-site
vcftools --vcf data/VCF/temp/MUN.F13.recode.vcf --out data/VCF/MUN.F13 --het

Final thresholds values for filtered data set MUN:

  • minimum sequence quality (minQ): 20
  • minimum genotype call rate per locus (geno): 90%
  • minimum minor allele count (mac): 3
  • minimum genotype depth (minD): 3
  • maximum missing data per individual (missInd): 50%
  • minimum minor allele frequence (maf): 0
  • mean minimum depth (m-minD): 15
  • mean maximum depth (m-minD): 75
  • dDocent filters run for allelic balance, Forward/Reverse and paired status, depth/quality ratio and maximum mean depth
  • Indels removed from data set
  • minimum genotype call rate by population: 90%

Have not yet filtered for HWE or Fis as indication of contamination

Data set contains 38418 SNP sites on 729 and individuals.

  theme_standard

Flag loci that are flagged as potential paralogs in > 2 individuals.

count(hap_stats, Poss_Paralog > 2)

Poss_Paralogs <- filter.loci.paralogs(hap_stats, 2)

84 loci were flagged as possible paralogs.

Number of SNPs & Haplotypes per locus

Each locus varies in the number of SNPs detected which determines the number of haplotypes expected in that population.

ggplot(hap_stats, aes(x = Sites)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, color = "black", fill = "grey95") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(Sites, na.rm = TRUE)),
                 color = "darkred", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = 25),
                 color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  labs(x = "number of SNPs per contig") +
  theme_standard

Filtering loci based on number of SNPs contained on that locus could bias the data set as loci with high recombination may be removed. On the other hand, assuming an approximate length of 250 bp loci with more than 25 SNPs would mean that 10% of bases are a polymorphisms.

Notice that with higher number of SNP sites, loci also more probable to have been flagged as possible paralogs in multiple individuals (intersect seems to be around 15?).

count(hap_stats, Sites > 25)
NoSNps <- filter.loci.noSNPs(hap_stats, 25)

8 loci were flagged.

Assuming that mutation is the only mechanism resulting in new haplotypes, the maximum expected number of haplotypes per locus is number of SNPs N + 1.

p1 <- ggplot(hap_stats, aes(x = Haplotypes)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, color = "black", fill = "grey95") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(Haplotypes, na.rm = TRUE)),
                 color = "darkred", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = quantile(Haplotypes, .99)),
                 color = "darkred", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +

  theme_standard

Again, removing loci with unexpectedly high numbers of haplotypes may bias the data set, as loci with e.g.high recombination may be removed from the data set.

count(temp, xtra >= 10)
# create vector of loci to remove
NoHaps <- filter(temp, xtra >= 10) 
NoHaps <- NoHaps$Locus

20 loci were flagged for excessive number of haplotypes compared to the number of SNPs at that locus.

Low Coverage/Genotyping Error

After combining SNPs on the same contig during the haplotyping process, it is possible to observe fewer than the expected number of haplotypes based on the genotype call (heterozygote/homozygote). When this occurs, that genotype is coded as missing. For each locus the number of individuals for which is it flagged as a potential a potential genotyping error or suffering from null alleles due to low coverage detected for a given locus is recorded.

ggplot(hap_stats, aes(x = Low_Cov.Geno_Err)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, color = "black", fill = "grey95") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(Low_Cov.Geno_Err, na.rm = TRUE)),
                 color = "darkred", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = (nrow(hap_ind_stats)*0.05)),
                 color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  labs(x = "potential genotyping error") +
  theme_standard

Cut-off value to remove locus if flagged as potential genotyping error in 2 or more individuals.

# summary of count of possible genotyping errors
count(hap_stats, Low_Cov.Geno_Err > 2)
# create vector of loci to remove
Geno_Err <- filter.loci.geno_err(hap_stats, 2)

278 loci were flagged as potentially affected by genotyping error.

Flag problematic individuals

Loci that are not successfully haplotyped in an individual due to missing data, complex locus, haplotyped genotype is higher/lower than SNP haplotype in a given individual are coded as missing for that individual. Problematic individual can be identified as having an increased amount of missing data.

Individuals with low proportion of successfully haplotyped loci

ggplot(hap_ind_stats, aes(x = Prop_Success)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.01, color = "black", fill = "grey95") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(Prop_Success, na.rm = TRUE)),
                 color = "darkred", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = 0.5),
                 color = "darkblue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  labs(x = "proportion loci successfully haplotyped") +
  theme_standard

Problem individuals can be identified by choosing a cut-off value for the minium proportion of sucessfully haplotyped loci and excluding individuals below that threshold value.

# count individuals above set threshold
count(hap_ind_stats, Prop_Success < .8)
# create vector of indv to remove (choose cut-off)
PropSuccessInd <- filter.ind.prop_success(hap_ind_stats, .8)
write.table(PropSuccessInd, "results/propSucc.indv", 
            col.names = TRUE, row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE, sep = "\t")
View(as.data.frame(PropSuccessInd))

Heterozygosity and HWE

Generate summary statistics

Inds <- as.data.frame(indNames(gen)) %>%
  rename(SAMPLE_ID = `indNames(gen)`) %>%
  separate(SAMPLE_ID, into = c("POP", "temp"), sep = "_", remove = FALSE) %>%
  select(-temp)
strata <- Inds
strata(gen) <- strata
# define groups using strata information
setPop(gen) <- ~POP
popNames(gen)
[1] "AFL" "BSL" "JKF" "SLT" "ULM"
# generate genetic diversity stats
GenDiv <- adegenet::summary(gen)
dat <- hierfstat:::.genind2hierfstat(gen)
GenDiv2 <- basic.stats(dat)

Compare observed (Ho) and expected (He) heterozygosity for all individuals across all populations.

# observed heterozygosity per locus
Ho <- as.data.frame(GenDiv$Hobs) %>% 
  rownames_to_column("LOCUS") %>%
  rename(Ho = `GenDiv$Hobs`)
# expected heterozygosity per locus
Hs <- as.data.frame(GenDiv$Hexp) %>% 
  rownames_to_column("LOCUS") %>%
  rename(Hexp = `GenDiv$Hexp`)
# expected and observed heterozysity per locus
Het <- left_join(Ho, Hs, by = "LOCUS")
# plot Ho vs Hs across all individuals
ggplot(Het, aes(x = Ho, y = Hexp)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, color = "red", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  xlim(0, 1) +
  ylim(0, 1) +
  labs(x = "observed heterozygosity Ho", y = "within cluster diversity Hs (Hexp)") +
  theme_standard

Test for deviations from Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium within each group (POP level):

setPop(gen) <- ~POP
# create one genind object per sample location
gen_seppop <- seppop(gen)
gen_AFL <- gen_seppop$AFL
gen_BSL <- gen_seppop$BSL
gen_JKF <- gen_seppop$JKF
gen_SLT <- gen_seppop$SLT
gen_ULM <- gen_seppop$ULM
# test for deviations from HWE overall and per region (B = no. of replicates)
HWE_test <- hw.test(gen, B = 1000)

Format output and view results:

# format put to combine p-values into one data frame
HWE <- as.data.frame(HWE_test) %>%
  select(Pr.exact) %>%
  rename(HWE = Pr.exact) %>%
  rownames_to_column("LOCUS")
HWE_AFL <- as.data.frame(HWE_test_AFL) %>%
  select(Pr.exact) %>%
  rename(HWE_AFL = Pr.exact) %>%
  rownames_to_column("LOCUS")
HWE <- left_join(HWE, HWE_AFL)
HWE_BSL <- as.data.frame(HWE_test_BSL) %>%
  select(Pr.exact) %>%
  rename(HWE_BSL = Pr.exact) %>%
  rownames_to_column("LOCUS")
HWE <- left_join(HWE, HWE_BSL)
HWE_JKF <- as.data.frame(HWE_test_JKF) %>%
  select(Pr.exact) %>%
  rename(HWE_JKF = Pr.exact) %>%
  rownames_to_column("LOCUS")
HWE <- left_join(HWE, HWE_JKF)
HWE_SLT <- as.data.frame(HWE_test_SLT) %>%
  select(Pr.exact) %>%
  rename(HWE_SLT = Pr.exact) %>%
  rownames_to_column("LOCUS")
HWE <- left_join(HWE, HWE_SLT)
HWE_ULM <- as.data.frame(HWE_test_ULM) %>%
  select(Pr.exact) %>%
  rename(HWE_ULM = Pr.exact) %>%
  rownames_to_column("LOCUS")
HWE <- left_join(HWE, HWE_ULM)
write.table(HWE, "results/HWEbypop",
            row.names = FALSE, col.names = TRUE, quote = FALSE)
# gather data into long format
HWE_long <- HWE %>%
  select(-HWE) %>%
  gather(POP, pval, 2:6) %>%
  mutate(HWE = ifelse(pval <= 0.05, "OUT", "IN"))
# plot data
ggplot(HWE_long, aes(x = HWE, position = "identity")) +
  geom_bar(color = "black", fill = "grey95") +
  labs(x = "significant deviation from HWE (p > 0.05)", y = "number of loci") +
  facet_grid( ~ POP) +
  theme_standard

Run PCA to identify outlier individuals

PCA

Scale alleles & perform PCA.

gen
/// GENIND OBJECT /////////

 // 159 individuals; 3,682 loci; 17,996 alleles; size: 14.4 Mb

 // Basic content
   @tab:  159 x 17996 matrix of allele counts
   @loc.n.all: number of alleles per locus (range: 2-30)
   @loc.fac: locus factor for the 17996 columns of @tab
   @all.names: list of allele names for each locus
   @ploidy: ploidy of each individual  (range: 2-2)
   @type:  codom
   @call: .local(x = x, i = i, j = j, loc = ..1, drop = drop)

 // Optional content
   @pop: population of each individual (group size range: 25-42)
   @strata: a data frame with 2 columns ( SAMPLE_ID, POP )
# create matrix with centered/scaled allele frequencies 
# will also replace missing data
X <- scaleGen(gen, NA.method = "mean")
# perform PCA/retain top 3 PCs
PCA <- dudi.pca(X, center = FALSE, scale = FALSE,
                scannf = FALSE, nf = 10)

Plot eigenvalues of first 25 principle components.

# extract Eigenvalues of each PC & calculate % variance explained by each PC
eig <- eigenvalues(PCA)
# plot %variance explained by of top 25 PCs
plot.eigen.variance(eig)

Analyze PCA results

Top three principle components retained, which explain a cumulative round(sum(eig$Percent[1:3])*100, digits =1)% variance.

Plot individuals by first two principle components

# Individuals' contribution to PCs/calculate Loading per individual and PC
PC_ind <- PC.ind(PCA) %>%
  rename(SAMPLE_ID = LIB_ID)
# join individuals' contribution to PC with strata
PC_ind <- left_join(PC_ind, strata)
ggplot(PC_ind, aes(x = Axis1, y = Axis2, color = POP)) +
  geom_point(shape = 1, size = 3) +
  labs(x = paste("PC1:", round(eig[1, 3], digits = 2), "%"), y = paste("PC2:", round(eig[2, 3], digits = 2), "%")) +
  theme_standard
